-- Test various oracle types

cell seed
  yield data = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6]

cell sort-json
  given seed.data
  yield sorted
  ---
  Sort «data» in ascending order. Output ONLY a JSON array of numbers, nothing else.
  ---
  check sorted is valid json array
  check~ sorted is a permutation of data
  check~ sorted is in ascending order

cell summarize
  given seed.data
  given sort-json.sorted
  yield report
  ---
  The original data was «data» and the sorted result is «sorted». Write a JSON object with fields: "count" (number of elements), "min" (smallest), "max" (largest), "sorted" (the sorted array).
  ---
  check report is not empty
